
ðŸ”¹ What is a Container?

A container is the most basic layout element in Bootstrap.
Itâ€™s used to wrap site contents, providing proper alignment and padding.

ðŸ§© Types of Containers
Type	Description	Example
.container	Fixed-width container that adapts to breakpoints	Centered content
.container-fluid	Full-width container spanning the entire viewport	Stretches across screen
.container-{breakpoint}	Container with width 100% until a specific breakpoint	.container-sm, .container-md, etc.
ðŸ’» Example Code
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Bootstrap Container Example</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>

  <!-- Fixed Container -->
  <div class="container bg-light text-center p-3 my-3 border">
    <h3>Fixed Container</h3>
    <p>This container adjusts width at each breakpoint.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Fluid Container -->
  <div class="container-fluid bg-info text-white text-center p-3">
    <h3>Fluid Container</h3>
    <p>This container spans the entire width of the screen.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Responsive Container -->
  <div class="container-md bg-warning text-dark text-center p-3 my-3">
    <h3>Container-MD</h3>
    <p>100% wide until medium screen size.</p>
  </div>

</body>
</html>

ðŸ§  Notes

.container provides fixed width.

.container-fluid covers full width always.

.container-{breakpoint} adjusts width up to the given breakpoint.

Containers include default horizontal padding (15px on each side).

Containers can be nested inside others for layered layouts.
